  "text": "Clearly, from reference to Fig. 1 , Uranium proves not to be such a successful elemental component with which to distinguish between samples from these two sites. Samples 1-4 derived from Arborfield Bridge [CITATION_1] have a Uranium content of approximately 1.4 ppm whilst the samples from Simon's Wood have a Uranium content of approximately 1.0 ppm. However, in the previous paper [CITATION_2] , the samples from the Arborfield Bridge (10-14) contain a higher level of Uranium (approximately 1.7 ppm), whilst the samples from Simon's Wood are found to have a very similar level to the Arborfield Bridge samples 1-4 of approximately 1.4 ppm. The grey area portrayed in our Fig. 1 demonstrates the similarity between samples 1-4 from Arborfield Bridge and samples 10-14 from Simon's Wood. Thus, the Uranium content does not appear to discriminate between all of the soil samples derived from each of these two distinct sites.",
